00:53.887 --> 00:57.758
ELIZABETH:Last summer, I started
getting these panic attacks.

00:57.791 --> 01:00.928
My homeopath told me
I was working too hard,

01:00.961 --> 01:04.897
burning the candle at both ends.

01:04.932 --> 01:07.401
As a treatment, he recommended
that I do something creative

01:07.435 --> 01:14.775
to release negative energy,
so I painted this last fall.

01:15.476 --> 01:17.611
What do you think about...

01:17.645 --> 01:21.582
staying here from now on?

01:29.623 --> 01:32.593
I know it's only
been a couple months but...

01:36.430 --> 01:38.999
You make me so happy...

01:41.001 --> 01:44.104
I feel...

01:44.138 --> 01:47.441
Free... with you.

02:08.696 --> 02:10.464
ELIZABETH: These are for you.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.769
For the place.

02:15.803 --> 02:17.938
ELIZABETH: And the convertible.

02:17.971 --> 02:20.808
Meet me back here at six?

02:45.566 --> 02:52.206
(people chatting)

03:55.269 --> 03:56.437
(Elizabeth sighs)

04:04.445 --> 04:08.248
(cars honking)

04:08.282 --> 04:11.485
RANDOM DRIVER:
Such a stupid asshole!

04:42.483 --> 04:45.953
... ave and Wallace st
right on the corner...

04:52.793 --> 04:56.464
(nervous crying)

06:37.130 --> 06:41.268
(police sirens)

07:00.454 --> 07:09.763
(*loud nightclub music)

07:20.107 --> 07:21.909
(water running)

07:21.942 --> 07:29.617
(paper towel dispensing)

07:32.853 --> 07:35.589
GIRL: Hey, do you
think you could-

07:35.623 --> 07:45.633
(*nightclub music)

07:45.666 --> 07:51.471
(*nightclub music)

08:08.822 --> 08:19.567
(partygoers laughing)

08:21.234 --> 08:25.405
(loud sniffing)

08:32.412 --> 08:34.181
(sniff)

08:37.049 --> 08:39.219
Yeah make it bigger...

08:39.852 --> 08:41.688
Wooo!!!

08:43.023 --> 08:45.525
(coughing and laughter)

08:46.526 --> 08:48.729
Oh hey, man how's it going?

08:51.765 --> 08:53.233
You work here?

08:56.536 --> 08:58.606
You uh...

08:59.206 --> 09:00.874
You want some?

09:09.883 --> 09:11.218
(loud sniffing)

09:11.251 --> 09:15.355
Fuck man, you scared us
for a minute there buddy.

09:15.388 --> 09:18.225
You came in like
'The Terminator'

09:18.258 --> 09:19.392
Fucking guy...

09:19.426 --> 09:22.095
Look uh...
you gotta try some of this.

09:23.263 --> 09:26.199
They call it Genuine Pink Dove

09:26.233 --> 09:30.203
or some shit like that.

09:30.237 --> 09:31.905
(smacks lips)

09:32.239 --> 09:34.908
Go for it.

09:41.414 --> 09:44.384
ROB: All right 'Terminator',

09:44.417 --> 09:47.755
... I'll see you
on the other side.

09:48.155 --> 09:48.789
(another loud sniff)

09:48.822 --> 09:51.258
Yeah do another one.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.160
There you go.

09:58.131 --> 10:00.300
You're welcome.

10:00.333 --> 10:05.138
Hah! What the fuck.
That is so rude.

10:05.172 --> 10:05.773
PARTIER: Hit it!

10:05.806 --> 10:06.740
One more line.

10:06.774 --> 10:08.475
PARTIER: Hit it boy!

10:08.508 --> 10:10.844
Where's my hundred?

10:11.679 --> 10:13.781
Where's my fucking hundred?

10:13.814 --> 10:20.453
(*loud nightclub music)

10:39.973 --> 10:49.549
(thunder)

11:08.702 --> 11:10.503
(screams in pain)

11:16.910 --> 11:22.349
(grunting and writhing in pain)

11:56.750 --> 12:00.387
(door opening)

12:45.165 --> 12:49.269
(birds chirping)

12:57.110 --> 12:59.346
(thunderclap)

12:59.379 --> 13:05.485
(crows cackling)

13:10.123 --> 13:15.628
(thunder)

13:41.021 --> 13:44.157
(panting)

13:45.658 --> 13:47.995
Excuse me. Do you have the time?

13:48.395 --> 13:50.330
(grunts painfully)

13:54.167 --> 13:57.037
You feeling alright?

14:02.375 --> 14:06.246
Perhaps I'm just taken
by how beautiful you are.

14:06.279 --> 14:09.682
Ahh.

14:10.750 --> 14:14.521
Honestly, it's been a week.

14:16.023 --> 14:18.358
Tell me about it.

14:27.534 --> 14:29.502
I've been coming here a lot...

14:29.536 --> 14:34.607
and between sitting
at my father's side...

14:34.641 --> 14:38.445
He slipped away
while holding my hand.

14:39.279 --> 14:42.916
At least you
got to say goodbye.

14:43.550 --> 14:46.019
Did you lose somebody?

14:46.053 --> 14:50.090
Uhhh... I lost my mother.

14:50.723 --> 14:52.559
I'm sorry.

14:52.592 --> 14:54.427
Hah... Azaria.

14:54.461 --> 14:55.262
What is?

14:55.295 --> 14:57.697
My name sorry, it's Azaria.

14:57.730 --> 14:59.732
Spence.

15:32.265 --> 15:33.933
(laughs)

16:10.137 --> 16:11.671
(doorbell)

16:19.346 --> 16:21.648
Oh my goodness,
you're so sweet.

16:21.681 --> 16:24.984
Hi.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.987
I can take those.

16:29.822 --> 16:32.692
You have such a beautiful smile.

16:33.493 --> 16:35.162
Come on in.

17:33.220 --> 17:35.388
I love the flower you brought.

17:35.422 --> 17:36.889
Lily.

17:36.923 --> 17:38.057
You know,

17:38.091 --> 17:40.893
I didn't think you
were listening...

17:41.594 --> 17:46.866
This house is immaculate.
It's worth a fortune.

17:46.899 --> 17:50.437
Yes it is my father's obsession.

17:52.239 --> 17:53.039
Cheers.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.407
(clink)

19:32.071 --> 19:34.974
(thunder)

19:35.007 --> 19:37.310
(panicked gasping)

19:37.344 --> 19:39.846
(loud thunder)

19:41.714 --> 19:43.683
AZARIA: Hey! Spence!

19:43.716 --> 19:44.651
Hey!

19:44.684 --> 19:45.685
(THUNDERCLAP)

19:45.718 --> 19:48.521
(THUNDERCLAP)
What's going on?!

19:55.728 --> 19:57.029
APRIL: There's
nothing wrong with you.

19:57.063 --> 19:58.898
It was just a panic attack.

19:58.931 --> 20:00.233
A panic attack.

20:00.267 --> 20:01.834
Yeah.

20:01.868 --> 20:02.902
All right then.

20:02.935 --> 20:04.337
Are you sure?
What about his heart?

20:04.371 --> 20:07.874
We did an EKG.
Checked his blood work.

20:07.907 --> 20:09.676
Palpitations can
come with anxiety.

20:09.709 --> 20:12.011
Are you under a lot of stress?

20:12.044 --> 20:15.715
Problems at home? Exams?

20:17.584 --> 20:19.752
His father just...
His father just died.

20:19.786 --> 20:25.925
Ah! Oh, I'm sorry.

20:25.958 --> 20:29.462
(bird cries)

20:38.405 --> 20:41.107
(door opens)

20:41.140 --> 20:42.709
JORY: ARG!

20:42.742 --> 20:43.410
AZARIA: Stop!

20:43.443 --> 20:45.044
Could you just relax!

20:45.077 --> 20:46.413
Relax?! You're out of line,

20:46.446 --> 20:47.614
and you're sleeping until
three in the afternoon!

20:47.647 --> 20:48.915
Will you stop for a second!

20:48.948 --> 20:51.083
Could you stop talking to
me like a fucking child?

20:51.117 --> 20:52.385
Jory, You know he's
coming in a couple days.

20:52.419 --> 20:54.621
Why can't you just help me?!

20:54.654 --> 20:57.123
JORY, PICK UP YOUR SHIT!

21:04.130 --> 21:06.633
Why don't you just get
Hitler's wet dream to help you?

21:10.437 --> 21:12.472
(nervous laughter)

21:13.440 --> 21:15.842
Ah... I'm sorry.

21:16.108 --> 21:20.480
Look at me.
It's okay.

21:20.513 --> 21:23.583
He's not doing well, so...

21:23.616 --> 21:26.986
So it falls on you?

21:27.019 --> 21:30.323
There's no one else.

22:06.393 --> 22:16.403
(taps spoon annoyingly)

22:18.405 --> 22:22.341
So does she give good head?

22:22.842 --> 22:27.046
Azaria forgot to mention what
you were in the nut house for.

22:33.720 --> 22:36.255
You should be more careful.

22:37.089 --> 22:40.727
You never know what
someone's got inside of them.

22:41.093 --> 22:43.396
I couldn't agree more.

23:11.924 --> 23:18.230
SPENCE: This stone...
It's radiant.

23:19.231 --> 23:24.403
I can almost feel it,
vibrating in my fingers.

23:25.972 --> 23:28.941
You feel that too?

23:30.142 --> 23:32.445
Yes.

23:32.479 --> 23:35.081
It was my mother's.

23:36.616 --> 23:39.085
I wear it when I need to.

23:42.121 --> 23:44.957
And why do you need to?

23:47.927 --> 23:51.464
Because I'm scared.

24:02.141 --> 24:05.478
I love you Spence.

24:07.146 --> 24:10.583
I love you too.

24:10.617 --> 24:13.452
(relaxed sigh)

24:22.862 --> 24:25.464
(electronic beeping)

24:33.806 --> 24:35.975
Okay.

24:38.811 --> 24:39.879
(laughter)

24:41.514 --> 24:43.716
Where are my keys?

24:49.488 --> 24:51.824
(laughter)

24:52.825 --> 24:54.493
Come here...

24:55.194 --> 24:57.329
I'll see you after class.

25:14.013 --> 25:19.719
(electronic beeping)

25:19.752 --> 25:20.587
(BANG)

25:21.353 --> 25:23.022
(pin drop)

25:51.217 --> 25:55.722
(low thunder)

26:05.097 --> 26:08.701
Finding what you're looking for?

26:08.735 --> 26:13.372
Azaria asked me to check
and make the safe was locked.

26:13.405 --> 26:15.574
No she didn't.

26:29.255 --> 26:31.958
What do you see in her?

26:35.461 --> 26:38.064
She's malleable,
easy to sway.

26:38.097 --> 26:40.633
I know, I gotta do it to
her all the time too.

26:46.338 --> 26:48.274
There's only one other person,

26:48.307 --> 26:51.010
who's made me
feel this way before.

26:54.180 --> 26:56.615
He went on a vacation,

26:56.649 --> 26:59.418
tropical cruise, with his wife.

26:59.451 --> 27:02.288
Two weeks later, he
arrives home by himself.

27:02.321 --> 27:06.759
Says she jumped.
Says she wanted to die.

27:06.793 --> 27:09.428
No one suspected that
this man did it himself.

27:09.461 --> 27:12.965
That he pushed her overboard.

27:13.465 --> 27:16.635
But somehow I knew it.

27:18.805 --> 27:23.509
That feeling...
I'll never forget it...

27:26.312 --> 27:30.182
JORY: My father is loaded.

27:30.216 --> 27:33.986
Like, fuckin' loaded.

27:36.322 --> 27:41.127
And what does that
have to do with me?

27:41.160 --> 27:43.863
AHHHH!!!!

27:53.672 --> 27:58.878
What's it like?
To not feel a god damn thing?

28:01.013 --> 28:04.383
It's a gift.

28:04.416 --> 28:07.086
God given...

28:07.419 --> 28:09.021
Hmm...

28:11.523 --> 28:13.692
You are a very
troubled young man,

28:13.726 --> 28:15.227
Jory.

28:15.261 --> 28:16.328
And I don't know what the fuck,

28:16.362 --> 28:18.397
you're getting
on about right now.

28:18.430 --> 28:21.734
If something were to happen,
if my father were to die,

28:21.768 --> 28:24.570
our inheritance
would be outstanding.

28:32.044 --> 28:35.247
I could give you
some for your help.

28:40.452 --> 28:43.022
Why are you
looking at me like that?

28:43.055 --> 28:47.259
You want me to help
you kill your father.

28:47.960 --> 28:50.897
He'll be here tomorrow.

28:51.430 --> 28:54.633
Boy, you're not
wasting any time.

28:55.234 --> 28:59.238
I'm talking about
fifty million dollars.

29:00.406 --> 29:03.309
And I'll give you
five hundred grand.

29:04.410 --> 29:07.713
It's gonna cost
you more than that.

29:07.746 --> 29:10.249
Five million?

29:16.088 --> 29:18.757
Ten million.

29:22.094 --> 29:25.932
When it's done, it's done.

29:25.965 --> 29:28.567
You don't mess with her.

29:28.600 --> 29:31.804
Fair enough.

29:38.845 --> 29:40.646
ARG!

29:41.447 --> 29:42.915
You fuck me over,

29:42.949 --> 29:47.753
you will be in the institution
for far longer this time.

29:47.786 --> 29:49.255
Or somewhere worse.

29:49.288 --> 29:50.456
AHHH!!!

29:51.790 --> 29:56.762
From this point forward,
your words mean nothing.

29:56.795 --> 29:59.665
Actions, Jory.

29:59.698 --> 30:02.634
Actions.

30:03.135 --> 30:06.505
(pen clicking)

30:23.990 --> 30:28.160
What happened in here?

30:30.062 --> 30:33.132
AZARIA: You vacuumed it
looks... It looks great.

30:33.165 --> 30:36.635
I believe the phrase
you're searching for is...

30:36.668 --> 30:38.137
Lemon fresh.

30:38.170 --> 30:40.506
I didn't know you knew where
the cleaning supplies were.

30:40.539 --> 30:45.344
I don't, Spence found them.
He's been earning his keep.

30:45.377 --> 30:47.846
AZARIA: Good boys.

30:48.180 --> 30:50.516
Where are you going
to be tomorrow night?

30:51.183 --> 30:53.819
I'm like a dandelion
caught in a breeze.

30:53.852 --> 30:56.655
Anywhere the wind blows.

30:56.688 --> 30:57.656
You should come for dinner.

30:57.689 --> 30:58.757
Okay, no, no.

30:58.790 --> 30:59.825
You don't think
Chuck would approve?

30:59.858 --> 31:01.393
No. I just I...

31:01.427 --> 31:03.162
I like this one. I don't
want to scare him off already.

31:03.195 --> 31:06.698
I'd love to come.
I'll bring the wine?

31:06.732 --> 31:08.734
Oh!!!

31:13.039 --> 31:16.042
You're in it now.

31:26.085 --> 31:30.689
I don't know what
you did... but thank you.

31:30.722 --> 31:33.725
There's no need to
thank me. He's a good kid.

31:33.759 --> 31:38.197
I don't know what
it is but, I get him.

31:38.230 --> 31:40.632
Come here.

31:48.474 --> 31:54.580
(thunder crash)

31:55.914 --> 31:57.083
SPENCE!
Talk to me.

31:57.116 --> 31:57.716
I'm fine.

31:57.749 --> 31:59.285
No you're not.

31:59.318 --> 32:01.220
Spence just look at me.Are you
okay? Spence what's going on?

32:01.253 --> 32:03.722
I'm fine...

32:03.755 --> 32:05.591
I'm fine.

32:11.430 --> 32:15.434
(grunting in pain)

32:50.536 --> 32:53.305
So why do you do this?

32:54.340 --> 32:56.775
I'm a sucker for
temptation I guess.

32:56.808 --> 32:59.811
I have a stark
raving mad sweet tooth.

33:00.546 --> 33:03.515
Put a cookie in
front of a five year old,

33:03.549 --> 33:05.484
what do you think
he's going to do?

33:05.517 --> 33:09.355
I was in the hospital
because I tried to kill someone.

33:11.357 --> 33:15.994
Stabbed him in the
neck with a steak knife.

33:17.229 --> 33:19.465
JORY: All I had to do was twist,

33:19.498 --> 33:22.868
and the lights would
have gone out but...

33:22.901 --> 33:28.006
JORY: But I just,
couldn't finish it.

33:28.040 --> 33:33.745
it was his eyes. I shouldn't
have looked at his eyes.

33:36.515 --> 33:40.552
Is this your way of telling
me you're getting cold feet?

34:11.083 --> 34:13.518
Smallest to biggest.

34:13.552 --> 34:15.554
I know.

34:44.483 --> 34:47.319
(door opens)

35:02.834 --> 35:05.937
Why aren't the lights
on in the driveway?

35:05.971 --> 35:08.474
I must have forgotten.

35:08.507 --> 35:11.410
Must have forgotten.

35:11.443 --> 35:15.281
What is it going to take?

35:15.314 --> 35:17.115
(laughing)

35:20.186 --> 35:21.753
Do you find me funny?

35:21.787 --> 35:25.424
I'm sorry. I can't help it.

35:25.457 --> 35:26.758
(mad cackling)

35:26.792 --> 35:29.495
Shall I wipe that
smile off your face?

35:29.528 --> 35:31.297
Wipe away.

35:31.330 --> 35:32.998
SPENCE: Mister Bowman.

35:33.031 --> 35:36.635
It's a pleasure to meet you sir.

35:36.668 --> 35:37.969
Who the hell is this?

35:38.003 --> 35:41.440
SPENCE: Spence Cutler.

35:41.473 --> 35:43.775
I enjoyed your
article in the Chronicle

35:43.809 --> 35:47.012
Marshall Taylor was
a mentor of mine at Georgetown.

35:52.218 --> 35:54.986
Then you have my
deepest sympathies.

35:59.491 --> 36:03.529
Well, shall we eat?

36:18.544 --> 36:21.046
Where's Spence?

36:21.079 --> 36:25.517
He and King Prick are sharing
some scotch in the cigar room.

36:25.551 --> 36:26.818
Well, you're doing a good job

36:26.852 --> 36:33.659
of not letting King
Prick get under your skin.

36:33.692 --> 36:36.362
Hang in there.
He'll be gone soon.

36:47.773 --> 36:49.575
We should go to the
lighthouse this weekend.

36:49.608 --> 36:50.942
You and me.

36:53.245 --> 36:55.947
Maybe Spence too.

37:04.923 --> 37:07.225
...and this
artifact here?

37:07.259 --> 37:09.361
Mmm...

37:09.395 --> 37:13.265
That, my boy,
is a Noh Mask,

37:13.299 --> 37:15.634
from the Medieval
Japanese Theatre.

37:16.134 --> 37:20.806
From a private collection
in Japan, 17th Century.

37:21.773 --> 37:26.878
This, particular treasure has
only been seen by a select few,

37:26.912 --> 37:31.450
and used in performance
on the rarest occasion.

37:31.483 --> 37:36.054
Amazing, how the mask
creates the illusion of emotion

37:36.087 --> 37:39.725
simply by how the
light touches it and the,

37:39.758 --> 37:45.130
calculated way
the actor tilts his head.

37:45.163 --> 37:48.300
The, essence of equanimity.

37:55.140 --> 37:57.142
Ahh...

38:07.853 --> 38:09.621
You know...

38:11.323 --> 38:15.494
If there's one, nugget
of advice that I can offer

38:15.527 --> 38:18.129
on the road
to great success

38:20.031 --> 38:25.437
it's exactly that.

38:25.471 --> 38:27.473
(piano roll)

38:27.506 --> 38:29.475
Equanimity.

38:30.141 --> 38:31.343
(laughs)

38:35.981 --> 38:38.517
It's a way of holding
thoughts with spaciousness

38:38.550 --> 38:41.987
the mind is engaged with the
world but not troubled by it.

38:46.558 --> 38:48.293
(clink)

38:48.326 --> 38:51.530
You've never even stood in the
same room with Marshall Taylor,

38:51.563 --> 38:53.832
let alone studied with him.

38:57.335 --> 39:00.305
And how would you know that?

39:00.338 --> 39:03.308
Because Taylor's
philosophy of equanimity

39:03.341 --> 39:07.413
is something a star
pupil of his would know.

39:08.246 --> 39:10.348
I don't know what to say.

39:12.851 --> 39:17.222
I think it would be in your
best interest to say something.

39:18.724 --> 39:21.359
Well, I have you
right where I want you.

39:21.393 --> 39:24.830
In this room.

39:24.863 --> 39:27.999
In this precise moment.

39:28.033 --> 39:30.769
And what
precisely are you after?

39:35.073 --> 39:37.509
Everything.

39:37.543 --> 39:44.082
SPENCE: your house, your cars,
your art collection,

39:44.115 --> 39:49.721
your furniture,
your daughter, your cash.

39:49.755 --> 39:52.357
Your fucking Noh Mask.

39:52.390 --> 39:56.962
Your life.
Everything. I'm taking it.

40:01.933 --> 40:03.969
Very thorough.

40:05.403 --> 40:08.106
I'm particularly
excited to get my hands

40:08.139 --> 40:10.609
on your dead
wife's necklace.

40:12.243 --> 40:14.646
(laughing)

40:17.282 --> 40:21.319
You parasite.

40:22.153 --> 40:24.222
You've had your sticky fingers

40:24.255 --> 40:26.424
in more than just my daughter.

40:28.126 --> 40:30.929
Daddy's little girl.

40:32.964 --> 40:34.933
You know,

40:34.966 --> 40:37.569
It's one thing to pull
the wool over the eyes

40:37.603 --> 40:40.071
of that naive little bitch,

40:40.105 --> 40:42.574
but I'm curious as to
what makes you think

40:42.608 --> 40:46.745
that I would ever
let you walk out of-

40:46.778 --> 40:50.448
walk...
walk out of her alive.

40:50.682 --> 40:52.784
Are you okay Chuck?

40:54.620 --> 40:56.988
What the hell
is happening to me?

40:57.355 --> 40:58.957
Goddammit!

40:59.457 --> 41:02.160
What have you done?

41:22.047 --> 41:23.348
(shudders)

41:34.159 --> 41:36.227
AZARIA: Spence?
Are you down here?

41:37.162 --> 41:38.463
Spence.

41:38.496 --> 41:39.998
